The course deals with general questions of non-sontractual obligations and with special types of non-contractual obligations (public promise to pay, presentation of thing, negotiorum gestio, unjustified enrichment, unlawful causing of damage).Objectives/eesmärkid:  The general purpose of the subject ist to provide to the students the fundamental knowledge of non-contractual obligations law, to explain the basic theoretical and practical problems and their solutions.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course student After passing trough the subject, the student must be able: 1) to understand the connections of the non-contractual obligations, also to distinguish the non-contractual obligations from the other obligations, 2) compose the analysis and solution of the training case of non-contractual obligations, 3) to expound the law of non-contractual obligations.
